    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Iran Appeals for Afghan Peace</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <dateline>TEHERAN, Iran, July 27</dateline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Iran appealed today for an end to the fighting in Afghanistan and said it did not discriminate between the Sunni and Shiite warring factions. The appeal was made by the Iranian Deputy Foreign Minister for Asian Affairs, Allaedin Boroujerdi, who met with leaders of the Hezb-i-Wahadat, who were trained in Iran, and with the Afghan President, Burhanuddin Rabbani, in Kabul, the official news agency said.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
